The savages who live in hidden wilds generally eat their food without salt, as there are no salt- pits there3 and this is, in my opinion, the rea- son that so many of them are afflicted with cutaneous disorders. Others burn a shrub which the Spaniards call la vidriera, the ashes of which they used instead of salt, to season their meat with and to prepare medicineS.
